						               													<description>Over last 9 years since premiere author of &amp;quot;Show Business&amp;quot; has been listening carefully to below complaints of the players:&amp;#10;- The game is too long;&amp;#10;- The rulebook is a nightmare;&amp;#10;- There's no Player Aid;&amp;#10;- For such heavy economic game the luck factor is unacceptable;&amp;#10;- The prints on Trend dice wipe off.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And here you go! &amp;quot;Tycoons&amp;quot; - the expansion to &amp;quot;Show Business&amp;quot; responds to all above complaints and delivers:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- A deck of brand new cards with 6 new, very powerful CHARACTERS along with compatibility reprint of 80 cards from basic game;&amp;#10;- Completely redesigned, improved and reprinted Rulebook of basic game (hope this time it will be the fastest comprehensible reading ever :-) );&amp;#10;- Brand new Player Aids;&amp;#10;- Fine tuning of elements that made first edition of &amp;quot;Show Business&amp;quot; a bit chaotic and luck dependent (due to unpredictible hostile actions and overall randomness). Now the game gives much more support to counteract hostile actions of your opponents and concentrate steadily on career of your band.&amp;#10;- 3 different time scenarios: short for newbies (40 to 100 min), medium for regular players (60 to 150 min) and extended for fans (80 to 200 min). The low values show play time for 2 players the high for 5. Decide yourself how much time you want to play and go on;&amp;#10;- Stickers for Trend Dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Tycoons&amp;quot; will be distributed as a standalone package for owners of basic game as well as an expansion integrated in one box with basic &amp;quot;Show Business&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;Give it a second chance or brand new try and enjoy!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
